featured_reviews.review_id:
The name of this masjid is MARKAZI QADEEM JAMIA MASJID Sharif, located at Duderhama Ganderbal. The word QADEEM in itself is self explanatory and reflects how old this masjid Sharif is.

Overall the location of this masjid is very well placed and is centrally located, just a kilometre away from the central market beehama.

The prayer space of this masjid Sharif is very vast and easily caters to the local demand, more space will be soon available as this masjid is undergoing a complete facelift, which will also add to its accommodating capacity. Besides this, cleanliness, comfort level, and accessibility for individuals with disabilities is also good.

Furthermore, the ablution and space for keeping shoes and belongings is also well maintained. The overall experience is completely different, pleasing and moving.

featured_reviews.review_id:
Markazi Qadeem Jamia Masjid Duderhama , considered to be one of the oldest mosques of the locality is loacted along the roadside of Dudrehama Ganderbal road. This mosque has also a Muslim cemetery in its vicinity and the community surrounding the mosquito comprises of Muslims. It can accommodate couple of hundred Muslims to offer congregational prayers on Fridays. This mosque is provided with all basic facilities like Wazu Khana (Bathroom) and during winter Hamam is used to keep water warm for  ablution. Nowadays it is under renovation.
Considering its location, it is ideally loacted and offers a huge folk an opportunity to attend prayers on time including the staff as well as students of central University of Kashmir(  science campus ) which is also located in its vicinity.

featured_reviews.review_id: Jama Masjid Mosque is a mosque in Srinagar, Jammu and Kashmir, Kashmir. The Jama Masjid of Srinagar is at Nowhatta, in the middle of the old city. It was built by Sultan Sikandar shah kashmiri shahmiri in 1394 AD Later, the son of Sultan Sikandar, Zain-ul-Abidin got the mosque extended the masurement of masjid is 381 ft by 384 ft built in area of 1,46,000 sqf The attractions of the Jama Masjid with is unique architecture,has mejistic courtyard and 378 wooden Deodar pillars supporting wooden ceiling with 346 pillars of 21 feet in height and 5 feet in girth and 32 pillars with 48 feet in height and 6 feet in girth. Another feature of the mosque is the peace and tranquility inside it, standing out against the hustle of the old bazaars around it. The masjid has a fountain also measurement of 33 feet by 34 feet which is also used for wadu (ablution) Thousands of Muslims assemble at the mosque every Friday to offer their prayers. This Jama Masjid of Kashmir, has seen a number of destructions till date. It got ruined thrice in fire and was reconstructed every time. The last restoration was carried out during the reign of Maharaja Pratap Singh.
